[1] Cholera: Burundi (Bujumbura)
Date: Mon 2 Jan 2023
Source: Xin Hua [edited]
https://english.news.cn/20230102/528d90da89e84d969f811b48bbeaef43/c.html


Burundi declares cholera outbreak
---------------------------------
Burundian Public Health and AIDS Control Minister Sylvie Nzeyimana on Sunday evening [1 Jan 2023] declared an outbreak of cholera in the east African country's commercial capital Bujumbura, she said here in a press release.

"Nine suspected cholera cases were identified on 30 Dec 2022 in the northern health district in the commercial capital Bujumbura with symptoms of diarrhea and vomiting, mainly in Bukirasazi neighborhood in Kinama zone. The next day, 2 other suspected cases were identified in Mutakura neighborhood, close to Bukirasazi," said Nzeyimana in the statement.

According to her, another suspected case was notified in Buyenzi, near the Bujumbura city center and the latter had been in contact with 1 of the suspected cases located in the north of Bujumbura.

"Results of the National Public Health Institute (INSP) issued on 31 Dec 2022 have confirmed that it was cholera. Today [2 Jan 2023], we take this opportunity to announce that 5 cholera patients are hospitalized at Prince Regent Charles Hospital while 7 others have already been discharged from hospital," said Nzeyimana.

Nzeyimana said that some preventive measures have already been taken. According to her, they include disinfecting infected households, sensitizing the community on the risks of the epidemic propagation and behavior to be adopted, and the search for other cholera cases in the community.

The cholera outbreak happens at a time when heavy rains hit several parts of Bujumbura and its surroundings from 26 to 31 Dec 2022, causing overflows of toilets. The Burundian health ministry has also banned the sale of cooked and raw food products on the streets in Bujumbura following the disease outbreak.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED from HealthMap Alerts

[Bujumbura, formerly Usumbura, is the economic capital, largest city and main port of Burundi. Bujumbura was formerly the country's normal capital. The city is on the northeastern shore of Lake Tanganyika. - Mod.LL]

