[3] Cholera: Nigeria (Ebonyi)
Date: Mon 2 Jan 2023
Source: ABN-TV [edited]
http://abntv.com.ng/news/nine-reported-dead-others-hospitalized-as-cholera-outbreak-hits-ebonyi/


Nine Reported Dead, Others Hospitalized As Cholera Outbreak Hits Ebonyi
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
In Akpoha hamlet, Afikpo North Local Government Area of Ebonyi State, there have been 9 cholera-related deaths. Numerous residents in the neighborhood have been admitted to the hospital and are currently receiving treatment. According to official records, there are 30 patients in the hospital, but locals believe there may be more.

On Sunday [1 Jan 2023], the state administration dispatched a State Rapid Response Team to the area to assist in stabilizing the situation. The delegation, which included employees from the National Center for Disease Control (NCDC) and the state department of health, was led to the town by Uchenna Ibiam, the chairperson of the local government.

The leader of the council expressed worry over the unexpected deaths, some of which were child deaths, in his remarks to the village elders, men, women, and youth of the Akpoha community. He asked the locals to maintain their composure because everything is in order. He praised the state administration for acting quickly, particularly in dispatching the Rapid Response Team to help the Akpoha Health Workers handle the issue.

[Byline: Kingsley Mecha]

