[4] Cholera: Kenya (Kitui)
Date: Thu 5 Jan 2023
Source: Kenya Broadcasting Corporation [edited]
https://www.kbc.co.ke/county-news/kitui/article/34283/health-authorities-confirm-outbreak-of-cholera-in-kitui


Health authorities confirm outbreak of cholera in Kitui
-------------------------------------------------------
Health authorities in Kitui County have confirmed the outbreak of cholera in Kalulu village, Kaghui area in Kyuso. However, Kyuso Sub-County Medical Officer of Health, Dr. Stephen Kioli, confirmed that stringent sanitary and hygiene measures have been put in place in the affected areas to curb the spread of the malady.

Dr. Kioli said out of the 4 samples they took from 4 patients, 2 were positive for cholera. The doctor said 3 other people who are believed to have come into contact with the sick were being held at the hospital for observation.

Dr. Kioli said high hygiene was the 1st line prevention measure and thus people were being encouraged to regularly wash their hands and not to eat fresh food without properly washing them.

On Tuesday [3 Jan 2023], public health officials and police officers visited the affected Kavonokya sect families and found 6 people suspected to be suffering from cholera and took them to Kyuso hospital for admission.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED from HealthMap Alerts

[Kitui is a town and capital of Kitui County in Kenya and is located 180 kilometers (112 mi) east of Nairobi. - Mod.LL]

